article.headline: Davis and Johnson Jr. each put up 19 points as Tennessee Tech takes down Tennessee State 70-50

images.name: Tennessee State Tigers vs. Tennessee Tech Golden Eagles: Game Highlights
images.caption: Tennessee State Tigers vs. Tennessee Tech Golden Eagles: Game Highlights

article.linkText: Davis and Johnson Jr. each put up 19 points as Tennessee Tech takes down Tennessee State 70-50
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- — Josiah Davis and Rodney Johnson Jr. each scored 19 points to lead Tennessee Tech over Tennessee State 70-50 on Tuesday night. Davis also added eight rebounds for the Golden Eagles (9-17, 4-9 Ohio Valley Conference). Johnson shot 7 for 13 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line. Diante Wood added 10 points. Christian Brown led the Tigers (15-11, 8-5) in scoring, finishing with 16 points. Jason Jitoboh added 11 points and 10 rebounds for Tennessee State. Kinyon Hodges also had eight points, eight rebounds and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
